dcterms:description: A ground motion dataset consisting of 85 synthetic ground motions used for benchmarking the proposed architecture's performance against the PhyLSTM3 model. The ground motion duration is 30 seconds, sampled at a frequency of 50 Hz, resulting in 1501 data points for each ground motion.
dcterms:title: Ground motion dataset used by Zhang for SDOF Boucwen system

dcterms:description: The PEER NGA-West2 database contains ground motion records used for nonlinear MDOF system analysis. The dataset includes 274 ground motions sampled at a frequency of 50 Hz, with a duration of 30 seconds, scaled to match a target design spectrum.
dcterms:title: PEER NGA-West2 database
